article.headline: S. Dakota St. 84, Mayville State 57
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. -- Chad White scored 15 points and South Dakota State defeated Mayville State 84-57 Wednesday night. The Comets, members of NAIA, took an early 10-3 lead and hung in for a while against the Jackrabbits (7-1). But the hosts ran off 10 straight points in a 2-minute stretch and led 43-30 at the half. Nate Wolters had 13 points and Dale Moss 12 for South Dakota State. Griffan Callahan grabbed nine rebounds and White had seven as the Jackrabbits owned a 51-29 edge on the boards. Shavonae Samuels scored 19 points to lead four players in double figures for Mayville State (4-4). Wiley Jiles scored 14, Ross Aman 11 and Dalonte Griffin had 10.
